@Node Usage " How do I "


OK, let's go straigth to the point:

    Running NoWB with no options causes it to run 'Setpatch' from c: and also execute the s:user-startup by default.

So, if you don't want the execution of it, just give an 'n' as an argument.


    Type ? as usual if you forgot this *huge* amount of options 8)


PROBLEMS:
--------

  · On slow HD's, my program may not work right ... If that's the case, then type 'd number' as an argument were number is the number (WOW) of seconds it takes to finish. -> If you want to know why this happens, read @{" How it works " link how}

  · NoWB writes on you HD, so it is wise to *always* wait for it to finish disk access before rebooting your computer. Anyway, if you forget this and your programs on the WBStartup drawer are not executed anymore after that, then run the supplied 'NoWBdoctor' program ...

@EndNode

