@Node how " The riddle is solved ... "


      OK, first of all, I would like to say that 'NoWB' is not a hack or patch ... It's just human intelligence versus CPU 'power' 8))

      When the AmigaDOS command 'LoadWb' is executed, the OS starts the GUI mode and runs whatever is on the 'WBstartup' drawer. What my program does when it is used instead of 'LoadWb' is to rename this directory to something else (WBST), and then execute 'LoadWb' -> now the DOS didn't find any program on the 'WBStartup' dir simply because this dir doesn't exists ;)

      Then we wait some seconds and undo the rename thing ... See the supplied source if your interested.


@Endnode
